TLS Certificate Renewal Failed
==============================

Hello {{idTag}},

We were unable to renew the TLS certificate for your {{instance_name}} tenant.

Domain:        {{domain}}
Expires at:    {{expiresAt}}
Days to expiry: {{daysUntilExpiry}}
Reason:        {{errorReason}}

{{#if suspended}}
*** YOUR TENANT HAS BEEN SUSPENDED ***
The certificate has expired and renewal is still failing, so HTTPS access to
your tenant is currently broken. As soon as a renewal succeeds, the
suspension will be lifted automatically.

{{/if}}
=== WHAT YOU NEED TO DO ===

The most common cause is incorrect DNS. Make sure the following DNS records
point at this server:

  * cl-o.{{idTag}}    (the API domain)
  * {{idTag}}         (the app domain)

Both should resolve to: {{localAddress}}

Either A records (for IP addresses) or CNAME records (for hostnames) work,
as long as the final answer matches one of the addresses above.

Once DNS is corrected, the next nightly renewal run will pick it up
automatically. If the certificate has not yet expired, you have until then
to fix it without further interruption.

If you continue to have problems, please contact your instance administrator.
